1
00:00:24,557 --> 00:00:30,096
PREVIOUSLY

2
00:00:30,163 --> 00:00:33,733
Since that day,
two sounds exist in my world.

3
00:00:34,734 --> 00:00:36,770
One is the sound everyone else hears.

4
00:00:38,238 --> 00:00:41,841
And another is the sound
that only I can hear.

5
00:00:44,277 --> 00:00:47,814
It was my dream to be a public defender.
How about you?

6
00:00:47,914 --> 00:00:50,183
I came here because of money.

7
00:00:50,316 --> 00:00:54,587
I wanted to become a lawyer
who stood up for the rights of the...

8
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:58,825
I heard public defenders make
around three to four million won a month.

9
00:01:00,293 --> 00:01:02,495
I saw someone who looks like you again.

10
00:01:03,930 --> 00:01:06,566
Where are you right now?

11
00:01:11,171 --> 00:01:15,175
If I meet you again, I will protect you.

12
00:01:17,610 --> 00:01:20,447
I will protect you.

13
00:01:21,948 --> 00:01:23,316
I miss you.

14
00:01:45,805 --> 00:01:47,240
Good.

15
00:02:00,386 --> 00:02:02,422
What was that sound?

16
00:02:07,927 --> 00:02:09,696
-What is it?
-What happened?

17
00:02:11,931 --> 00:02:13,967
What just happened?
Isn't that Double Nose?

18
00:02:14,234 --> 00:02:15,301
MUN DONG-HUI

19
00:02:16,169 --> 00:02:18,171
Oh my gosh.

20
00:02:19,005 --> 00:02:21,774
Guys, Seong-bin pushed her out the window.

21
00:02:22,642 --> 00:02:23,610
What?

22
00:02:23,743 --> 00:02:26,346
-Call the police!
-I will do it.

23
00:02:30,850 --> 00:02:31,918
What is this?

24
00:02:36,556 --> 00:02:39,192
Lawyers must be going through
hard times these days.

25
00:02:39,425 --> 00:02:42,495
The competition to be a public defender
is so fierce.

26
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:46,799
I know. What will you do about her?

27
00:02:48,368 --> 00:02:49,335
RESUME
JANG HYE-SEONG

28
00:02:49,402 --> 00:02:53,573
Oh, the one who got expelled
because of fireworks?

29
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:56,809
Her story was pretty impressive,
but I didn't like her much.

30
00:02:57,076 --> 00:02:58,211
Why?

31
00:02:58,311 --> 00:03:01,214
She took some public defense cases
as a private attorney.

32
00:03:01,314 --> 00:03:05,685
She has a bad reputation.
Her nickname is "20 Seconds."

33
00:03:05,885 --> 00:03:09,889
All she pleads is "The defendant
is repenting so please have mercy."

34
00:03:10,056 --> 00:03:14,093
All it takes is 20 seconds.
I am against hiring her.

35
00:03:14,260 --> 00:03:19,766
Please understand she lived a lonely life
after her mother had passed away.

36
00:03:19,899 --> 00:03:23,136
She passed away last year.

37
00:03:24,003 --> 00:03:27,473
Please understand she was in pain
after recently having lost her mother.

38
00:03:27,607 --> 00:03:31,244
But from her story,
she seemed quite promising.

39
00:03:31,611 --> 00:03:37,717
Her story was sad, and she was brave.
I think she has potential.

40
00:03:42,755 --> 00:03:45,925
I am a witness to this murder case.

41
00:03:46,993 --> 00:03:48,695
I am Jang Hye-seong.

42
00:03:49,696 --> 00:03:51,431
What do you think?

43
00:03:52,498 --> 00:03:57,837
I'm not sure. I can't tell
whether she is a good or bad attorney.

44
00:03:59,038 --> 00:04:00,273
I'm confused.

45
00:04:06,512 --> 00:04:08,514
ONE MONTH LATER

46
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:21,160
THE DAUGHTER OF HYE-SEONG'S CHICKEN
HAS BECOME A PUBLIC DEFENDER

47
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:24,864
HYE-SEONG'S CHICKEN

48
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:28,835
Shoot. I can't believe my mother.

49
00:04:33,072 --> 00:04:34,807
I told you not to hit my head.

50
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:39,479
What are all these?
Why did you put these up?

51
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:43,082
I'm proud that you're a lawyer
who gets paid by the government.

52
00:04:43,716 --> 00:04:46,886
You're at the same level
as prosecutors and judges.

53
00:04:47,453 --> 00:04:49,122
Just come with me.

54
00:04:49,622 --> 00:04:52,358
-Where are you going?
-Just come with me.

55
00:04:56,296 --> 00:05:00,500
Please look at this

56
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:05,071
Please look at my daughter

57
00:05:05,238 --> 00:05:07,473
Look at my pretty daughter

58
00:05:07,607 --> 00:05:10,910
You're just happy that
I'm going to pay you back.

59
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:13,179
It's not the money.

60
00:05:13,446 --> 00:05:17,317
I'm happy you became a public defender.

61
00:05:17,450 --> 00:05:20,119
Really? Then can I not pay you back?

62
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,322
-Hey!
-Mom!

63
00:05:22,889 --> 00:05:26,159
Don't hit my head! I'm old enough now.

64
00:05:26,359 --> 00:05:29,462
You're a public defender now.

65
00:05:29,862 --> 00:05:32,432
You have a long way to go from here.

66
00:05:32,598 --> 00:05:34,967
You should really get a hold of yourself.

67
00:05:35,301 --> 00:05:37,537
It won't be hard.
I chose it because it's easy.

68
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:40,873
-What?
-They will pay me every month.

69
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:42,809
And they will bring me cases, too.

70
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:46,813
I just have to ask for mercy.
It's a piece of cake.

71
00:05:47,246 --> 00:05:50,016
I'll get paid for a few years,
and then get married.

72
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:52,752
Stop hitting me!

73
00:05:53,052 --> 00:05:55,254
Don't you dare defend people like that.

74
00:05:55,455 --> 00:06:00,360
You could be the first lawyer
to be hit by her mother in court. Got it?

75
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:07,400
Stop putting them up.
It's nothing to be proud of.

76
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:10,937
-Did you get a room?
-I found one near the court.

77
00:06:11,437 --> 00:06:14,674
It's a rooftop house,
but it has two rooms and a bathroom.

78
00:06:15,408 --> 00:06:16,676
Good job.

79
00:06:17,110 --> 00:06:20,313
Why does it have to be Yeonju?
It's too far away.

80
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:23,516
You said you didn't care where I go,
as long as I get the job.

81
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:28,554
Are there any judges
or prosecutors you know there?

82
00:06:28,755 --> 00:06:32,492
Have you ever seen me making allies?
I don't need them.

83
00:06:32,992 --> 00:06:35,728
Mom, come on!

84
00:06:37,096 --> 00:06:38,331
YEONJU DISTRICT PROSECUTOR'S OFFICE

85
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:40,800
Say it! You pushed her!

86
00:06:46,472 --> 00:06:49,041
If you're going to confess anyway,
just confess it to me.

87
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:52,311
I'm one of the more polite people
around here.

88
00:06:52,512 --> 00:06:54,981
You would get a good beating
in other places.

89
00:06:58,418 --> 00:07:00,453
You pushed her, right?

90
00:07:04,323 --> 00:07:07,960
You were jealous that
she got picked up on the street.

91
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:12,365
That's why you bullied her
for having gotten plastic surgery.

92
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:15,368
And then you pushed her
off the fourth floor!

93
00:07:15,835 --> 00:07:18,938
A lot of kids said they saw it.
That's the fact.

94
00:07:19,038 --> 00:07:23,176
It's not the fact, you jerk!
I didn't know she was in the music room!

95
00:07:25,011 --> 00:07:27,814
I can't believe I'm stuck with this jerk.

96
00:07:27,914 --> 00:07:31,350
Hey! Stop denying the truth!

97
00:07:31,651 --> 00:07:34,854
Look. All your friends wrote statements!

98
00:07:36,222 --> 00:07:38,858
Sir, let me take over now.

99
00:07:39,892 --> 00:07:41,227
Who are you?

100
00:07:42,161 --> 00:07:44,730
Prosecutor Seo, you're going
to question her directly?

101
00:07:44,931 --> 00:07:46,265
Yes.

102
00:07:46,966 --> 00:07:48,267
Have this.

103
00:07:49,735 --> 00:07:52,472
I'm okay. I don't like mints.

104
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:54,207
You should still take it.

105
00:07:55,074 --> 00:07:59,679
A well-mannered person
doesn't let others know what he ate.

106
00:08:03,049 --> 00:08:06,452
Oh, my gosh. She totally got you!

107
00:08:06,686 --> 00:08:09,622
-This is so funny.
-Shut it!

108
00:08:11,257 --> 00:08:13,526
Seong-bin? Come with me.

109
00:08:16,896 --> 00:08:18,130
PROSECUTOR SEO DO-YEON

110
00:08:19,765 --> 00:08:20,933
Gosh.

111
00:08:21,901 --> 00:08:23,803
Your nails are amazing.

112
00:08:24,036 --> 00:08:26,239
I did them myself. Shall I do yours, too?

113
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:34,881
I got some sandwiches.

114
00:08:39,318 --> 00:08:43,689
So you didn't know
Mun Dong-hui was in the music room?

115
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:45,858
Of course I didn't know.

116
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:50,329
And even if I knew, I wouldn't have
pushed her off the fourth floor.

117
00:08:51,797 --> 00:08:55,201
I knew it. That would've been
considered attempted murder.

118
00:08:55,801 --> 00:08:57,436
You're not the type.

119
00:08:58,237 --> 00:09:00,339
Have some drinks. You'll get thirsty.

120
00:09:01,807 --> 00:09:05,044
So you never bullied Dong-hui, either?

121
00:09:05,444 --> 00:09:07,113
No. Never.

122
00:09:07,613 --> 00:09:09,815
I just gave her
the nickname "Double Nose."

123
00:09:10,116 --> 00:09:12,685
And it was just a joke.

124
00:09:13,119 --> 00:09:15,254
Did the kids laugh
when you called her that?

125
00:09:15,721 --> 00:09:18,357
Of course they did. Don't you get it?

126
00:09:18,491 --> 00:09:20,560
Double eyelids and a nose job,
so "Double Nose."

127
00:09:22,194 --> 00:09:24,096
I totally get it.

128
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:28,401
Did Dong-hui laugh
when you called her that?

129
00:09:29,802 --> 00:09:30,803
What?

130
00:09:31,370 --> 00:09:33,573
You said it was a joke.

131
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:37,410
Shouldn't the person involved find it
funny to be a joke?

132
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:41,814
If she didn't laugh,
it's not a joke. It's just bullying.

133
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:45,618
"Bullying"?

134
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,687
She has begun.

135
00:09:52,191 --> 00:09:55,061
It was a joke, but you're not laughing.

136
00:09:56,162 --> 00:09:58,598
Why is that? I see.

137
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,635
It must have been bullying.

138
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:11,210
Then I shouldn't joke either.

139
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:14,447
Right?

140
00:10:18,551 --> 00:10:21,253
Shall we get started?
You're Ko Seong-bin, right?

141
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:26,192
Do you know you're being
investigated for attempted murder?

142
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:31,864
You have the right to refuse
to say anything that might hurt you.

143
00:10:32,732 --> 00:10:34,333
And you can hire a lawyer.

144
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,668
AT A HIGH SCHOOL IN YEONJU...

145
00:10:35,735 --> 00:10:36,902
-What?
-No way.

146
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:38,037
That's crazy.

147
00:10:39,705 --> 00:10:42,141
So Ko Seong-bin was the one who did it.

148
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:43,376
-Hold on.
-Hold on.

149
00:10:43,509 --> 00:10:46,379
This isn't the time to be studying.
You'll be shocked to see this.

150
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:48,147
I won't be.

151
00:10:48,714 --> 00:10:51,617
You know Ko Seong-bin, right?
The one who has a crush on you.

152
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:52,918
I don't know. Don't care.

153
00:10:53,019 --> 00:10:55,988
Hey. Look at this first.

154
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:03,396
ATTORNEYS SELECTED FOR YEONJU DISTRICT
PUBLIC DEFENDER'S OFFICE

155
00:11:06,098 --> 00:11:08,167
ATTORNEY JANG HYE-SEONG
ATTORNEY CHA GUAN-WOO

156
00:11:10,102 --> 00:11:14,340
-No way.
-See? I said you would be shocked.

157
00:11:19,211 --> 00:11:23,149
Hey! Thank you so much!

158
00:11:25,184 --> 00:11:26,952
I have to go.

159
00:11:27,987 --> 00:11:29,422
Where are you going?

160
00:11:31,590 --> 00:11:34,026
Why is he thanking you
that Seong-bin got arrested?

161
00:11:34,593 --> 00:11:35,995
What did I do?

162
00:11:52,144 --> 00:11:55,181
-Hey!
-I'm sorry.

163
00:11:57,850 --> 00:11:59,618
I'm sorry.

164
00:11:59,752 --> 00:12:00,953
Did you just kiss me?

165
00:12:19,538 --> 00:12:21,207
COURTHOUSE

166
00:12:23,275 --> 00:12:25,211
ATTORNEYS SELECTED FOR YEONJU DISTRICT

167
00:12:25,311 --> 00:12:26,712
She hasn't changed at all.

168
00:12:26,946 --> 00:12:28,280
ATTORNEY JANG HYE-SEONG

169
00:12:35,221 --> 00:12:36,589
YEONJU DETENTION CENTER

170
00:12:49,068 --> 00:12:51,737
Jun-guk, don't you get out next week?

171
00:12:53,339 --> 00:12:55,508
Have you found work?

172
00:12:56,976 --> 00:12:57,977
Yes.

173
00:12:58,544 --> 00:13:00,946
A pastor said he would find me a job.

174
00:13:01,747 --> 00:13:03,349
I envy you.

175
00:13:04,250 --> 00:13:06,919
I guess the Bible actually provides a way.

176
00:13:09,255 --> 00:13:13,826
Should I read it from now on?

177
00:13:16,862 --> 00:13:20,466
What is this? Do you know them?

178
00:13:22,234 --> 00:13:23,269
Yes.

179
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:32,845
I sort of owe her something.

180
00:13:32,912 --> 00:13:35,014
SELECTED LAWYERS WITH
NONSTANDARD BACKGROUND

181
00:13:58,103 --> 00:14:00,940
Why did I have to dream
of him on my first day?

182
00:14:50,956 --> 00:14:53,058
DRUG USER'S LIMITED AMNESTY
CONFESSION PERIOD

183
00:14:59,231 --> 00:15:02,835
I kept calling you.
I followed you from the bus.

184
00:15:04,637 --> 00:15:05,938
Excuse me.

185
00:15:07,773 --> 00:15:10,542
You're not my type. Okay?

186
00:15:12,278 --> 00:15:15,347
Isn't this your wallet?
You dropped it on the bus.

187
00:15:18,384 --> 00:15:20,753
-It's not mine.
-What?

188
00:15:21,854 --> 00:15:24,290
I'll find the owner. Okay?

189
00:15:26,158 --> 00:15:29,795
What do you mean? I saw your ID in there.

190
00:15:30,195 --> 00:15:32,898
Oh, you must be embarrassed.

191
00:15:34,833 --> 00:15:38,771
Don't you remember me?
I'm Cha Guan-woo. We met before.

192
00:15:40,572 --> 00:15:41,907
I've never seen you before.

193
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:44,476
We met at the interview.

194
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:48,013
Don't you remember grabbing me
by the throat for questions?

195
00:15:48,213 --> 00:15:49,615
I don't remember.

196
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:55,321
I didn't realize it then,
but you're really pretty.

197
00:15:58,691 --> 00:16:00,392
Don't people say you look like someone?

198
00:16:00,993 --> 00:16:04,663
It's a foreign actress.
She has thick lips and big eyes.

199
00:16:05,331 --> 00:16:09,702
That's right! Jolie! Don't people say
you look like Angelina Jolie?

200
00:16:13,739 --> 00:16:15,174
Please keep your voice down.

201
00:16:20,112 --> 00:16:21,580
Why? It's a compliment.

202
00:16:22,414 --> 00:16:24,216
I'm just saying you're pretty.

203
00:16:26,218 --> 00:16:31,290
By the way, Hye-seong...
Should I call you Ms. Jang?

204
00:16:31,857 --> 00:16:34,827
No. That doesn't sound right.

205
00:16:35,260 --> 00:16:39,531
Ms. Jjang sounds better. Ms. Jjang!

206
00:16:42,401 --> 00:16:45,904
I believe becoming
a public defender was your dream.

207
00:16:46,071 --> 00:16:48,674
You're just embarrassed
to admit it. Right?

208
00:16:49,108 --> 00:16:53,212
I realized it a while ago.
You get mad when you're embarrassed.

209
00:16:54,947 --> 00:16:58,150
I think I know
why you signed up for Yeonju.

210
00:16:59,251 --> 00:17:00,386
Shall I guess?

211
00:17:02,955 --> 00:17:05,257
Is it because of Mr. Shin Sang-deok?

212
00:17:08,627 --> 00:17:11,330
I came here
because of Mr. Shin Sang-deok, too.

213
00:17:12,264 --> 00:17:16,101
He has been a public defender for
40 years. He is my role model.

214
00:17:16,602 --> 00:17:18,103
Is he yours, too?

215
00:17:19,304 --> 00:17:21,907
No!

216
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:25,344
You're Cha Guan-woo, right?

217
00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:30,549
I don't look like Angelina Jolie.
And I didn't know you would come here.

218
00:17:30,682 --> 00:17:32,151
I don't want to be called "Ms. Jjang."

219
00:17:32,251 --> 00:17:34,653
And I didn't come here
because of Shin Sang-deok.

220
00:17:34,787 --> 00:17:41,026
The old man with dentures
and a hearing aid isn't my role model!

221
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:52,704
Here you go.

222
00:17:55,874 --> 00:17:58,811
Are you Shin Sang-deok?

223
00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:00,979
Yes.

224
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:03,348
I'm sorry I didn't recognize you.

225
00:18:04,850 --> 00:18:06,385
You should apologize.

226
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:09,521
Why should I?

227
00:18:10,456 --> 00:18:15,294
Never mind. No need to apologize.
Everything you said is right.

228
00:18:16,195 --> 00:18:18,430
Are you the new public defenders?

229
00:18:18,797 --> 00:18:22,301
Yes, I'm Cha Guan-woo
and this is Jang Hye-seong.

230
00:18:23,435 --> 00:18:26,572
This is Officer Choi Yu-chang.
You should say hello.

231
00:18:26,738 --> 00:18:30,075
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

232
00:18:31,176 --> 00:18:32,511
Me, too.

233
00:18:33,779 --> 00:18:38,250
Let's all go out. I'll buy you coffee.

234
00:18:39,017 --> 00:18:40,085
Thank you.

235
00:18:41,220 --> 00:18:43,388
What are you doing? Let's go.

236
00:18:46,091 --> 00:18:48,894
Mr. Shin doesn't forget things easily.

237
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:51,130
For your sake, you should apologize soon.

238
00:18:55,834 --> 00:18:57,436
What's he going to do?

239
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:59,505
Is he going to bully me?

240
00:19:24,163 --> 00:19:25,297
Hold on.

241
00:19:27,533 --> 00:19:31,703
If you use this,
you don't have to use your saliva.

242
00:19:34,239 --> 00:19:35,674
Thank you, Mr. Shin.

243
00:19:38,377 --> 00:19:40,212
This really helps!

244
00:19:45,617 --> 00:19:49,621
Tell her it's the office at the end.
Yes, I'll go out now.

245
00:19:51,490 --> 00:19:53,192
Jo Yeong-sook.

246
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:55,627
Here it is.

247
00:19:56,562 --> 00:19:59,031
Charged with special larceny
and obstruction of justice.

248
00:19:59,398 --> 00:20:01,099
And she is deaf.

249
00:20:04,102 --> 00:20:06,171
-Come on in.
-Hello.

250
00:20:07,639 --> 00:20:09,942
You know sign language?

251
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:13,512
I thought I might need it.
I'm learning braille, too.

252
00:20:15,948 --> 00:20:17,082
Please come this way.

253
00:20:29,094 --> 00:20:30,128
Please wait.

254
00:20:32,397 --> 00:20:36,435
Ms. Jang, your client is here, too.
Shall I bring her in?

255
00:20:36,535 --> 00:20:37,703
Yes.

256
00:20:38,904 --> 00:20:40,205
Please come this way.

257
00:20:45,177 --> 00:20:46,478
Excuse me.

258
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:50,215
I'm Ko Seong-bin.

259
00:20:53,418 --> 00:20:54,720
TEXTBOOKS

260
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:10,802
Hello, I'm Park Su-ha. Remember me?

261
00:21:11,870 --> 00:21:13,872
What if she doesn't remember?

262
00:21:16,575 --> 00:21:18,477
It's been a long time. I'm Park Su-ha.

263
00:21:19,478 --> 00:21:21,346
That's too plain.

264
00:21:21,580 --> 00:21:23,315
I missed you, Hye-seong.

265
00:21:27,953 --> 00:21:29,588
This is so hard.

266
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:36,662
It's been a long time, Hye-seong.
Hye-seong.

267
00:21:38,697 --> 00:21:40,699
-No.
-What is he doing?

268
00:21:41,533 --> 00:21:42,467
He is crazy.

269
00:21:44,403 --> 00:21:45,637
What should I say?

270
00:21:45,837 --> 00:21:47,773
I didn't do it.

271
00:21:54,946 --> 00:21:57,749
Everyone who comes here
says the same thing.

272
00:21:59,217 --> 00:22:02,521
But look. There's too much evidence.

273
00:22:03,388 --> 00:22:05,824
And you lied to the prosecutor
that you're not the one.

274
00:22:06,458 --> 00:22:08,593
No wonder you were accused
of attempted murder.

275
00:22:08,827 --> 00:22:10,996
That's nonsense! "Attempted murder"?

276
00:22:11,863 --> 00:22:13,298
Why is it nonsense?

277
00:22:14,066 --> 00:22:17,302
The friend you wanted
to bully was sitting by the window.

278
00:22:20,305 --> 00:22:22,341
There was no one else in the room.

279
00:22:23,442 --> 00:22:24,743
You wanted to scare her.

280
00:22:24,910 --> 00:22:26,278
What is it?

281
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:28,547
But you decided that
you should kill her instead.

282
00:22:29,414 --> 00:22:32,551
But she didn't die,
and she is currently unconscious.

283
00:22:33,985 --> 00:22:36,855
If the victim dies,
then you'll be charged with murder.

284
00:22:37,222 --> 00:22:39,024
It's an attempted murder
because she is still alive.

285
00:22:39,591 --> 00:22:44,329
I can't believe this! Lady! I mean, miss!

286
00:22:44,496 --> 00:22:47,532
I did swear at kids and take their money.

287
00:22:47,632 --> 00:22:50,936
But it was all reasonable enough.
I never did something terrible.

288
00:22:51,036 --> 00:22:53,372
But attempted murder?
I really didn't do it!

289
00:22:53,939 --> 00:22:56,341
There are people who saw you pushing her.

290
00:22:56,408 --> 00:22:59,678
They are just lying
to get me into trouble!

291
00:23:02,714 --> 00:23:05,884
I am defending you
even if you don't pay me a cent.

292
00:23:06,118 --> 00:23:08,353
I can't help you if you act like this.

293
00:23:08,587 --> 00:23:10,188
Do you want to go
to a trial without a lawyer?

294
00:23:19,297 --> 00:23:23,301
Don't worry.
The truth always wins in court.

295
00:23:23,602 --> 00:23:25,604
I will show it to you.

296
00:23:35,247 --> 00:23:36,782
Please take care.

297
00:23:39,317 --> 00:23:42,721
With this much evidence,
you'll be found guilty.

298
00:23:42,988 --> 00:23:46,792
If you try to deny it,
it will only increase your sentence.

299
00:23:47,092 --> 00:23:49,928
You should admit it
and say that you're sorry.

300
00:23:50,362 --> 00:23:54,266
I'll say it was an accident.
Then you won't go to jail.

301
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:59,371
Will you keep denying it?
Or will you admit your guilt?

302
00:24:01,006 --> 00:24:03,442
I really didn't push her.

303
00:24:03,775 --> 00:24:06,144
I didn't even know
she was in the music room!

304
00:24:06,645 --> 00:24:10,849
I didn't do it. I really didn't do it.

305
00:24:13,518 --> 00:24:15,020
Are you going to keep denying it?

306
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:20,292
Do you want to rot in jail
while your friends have fun?

307
00:24:21,893 --> 00:24:26,031
Ms. Jjang. Don't force her.
Like she said--

308
00:24:26,131 --> 00:24:29,234
-This is my client.
-I know I shouldn't meddle, but--

309
00:24:29,334 --> 00:24:30,302
Then don't say anything.

310
00:24:30,435 --> 00:24:33,738
-I think I deserve to say--
-Nothing.

311
00:24:33,872 --> 00:24:37,442
Why not?
We are a team that works together.

312
00:24:37,542 --> 00:24:39,010
No, we're not.

313
00:24:44,683 --> 00:24:46,952
Guilty or not guilty? You choose.

314
00:24:49,821 --> 00:24:51,323
I can't be responsible for the result.

315
00:24:53,024 --> 00:24:58,330
Okay, I'm guilty! Okay? You jerk!

316
00:25:27,959 --> 00:25:31,296
-What about Ms. Jang?
-She wants to finish up.

317
00:25:32,898 --> 00:25:36,468
Mr. Shin, about what I said to Ms. Jjang,
I was right, wasn't I?

318
00:25:36,601 --> 00:25:39,738
-Of course you were.
-We can work as a team, right?

319
00:25:39,871 --> 00:25:40,839
Yes.

320
00:25:40,939 --> 00:25:43,575
The prosecutors have a great system.

321
00:25:43,708 --> 00:25:46,578
-We should work together, too.
-Of course.

322
00:25:46,711 --> 00:25:51,983
And even if no one else does,
a lawyer should believe his client.

323
00:25:56,555 --> 00:25:58,990
Did I say something wrong?

324
00:26:00,859 --> 00:26:02,160
The elevator is here.

325
00:26:08,266 --> 00:26:11,670
Don't you believe your clients, Mr. Shin?

326
00:26:11,770 --> 00:26:14,039
I try to believe them.

327
00:26:14,973 --> 00:26:18,510
But sometimes it can come back
to bite you.

328
00:26:18,810 --> 00:26:20,612
How can you say that?

329
00:26:20,812 --> 00:26:23,014
You have to believe them to defend them.

330
00:26:23,148 --> 00:26:25,216
I believe my client 100%.

331
00:26:25,584 --> 00:26:30,455
But if they are found lying,
it would be worse for them.

332
00:26:31,323 --> 00:26:33,858
My client would never lie.

333
00:26:34,159 --> 00:26:36,261
I can just tell.

334
00:26:36,628 --> 00:26:38,430
You can just tell?

335
00:26:39,097 --> 00:26:40,332
I envy you.

336
00:26:40,699 --> 00:26:43,535
I've worked for 40 years,
but I still can't tell.

337
00:26:45,637 --> 00:26:46,938
Forty years.

