00:27:42,427 --> 00:27:44,996
DIVORCE, TRAFFIC ACCIDENT PROFESSIONAL

349
00:27:49,067 --> 00:27:50,235
PUBLIC DEFENDERS

350
00:27:50,335 --> 00:27:54,339
"Public defenders. They total
only one percent of Korean lawyers.

351
00:27:54,539 --> 00:27:59,978
They defend those who cannot afford
to hire a lawyer.

352
00:28:00,478 --> 00:28:03,581
They work for the people, not for money."

353
00:28:10,922 --> 00:28:14,693
"I will not hide nor add to the truth.

354
00:28:15,627 --> 00:28:19,497
I will tell the truth
and if I were to lie,

355
00:28:20,665 --> 00:28:24,202
I swear that
I will be punished for perjury."

356
00:28:27,372 --> 00:28:29,074
What a perfect job for her!

357
00:29:05,376 --> 00:29:07,879
My head is about to burst.

358
00:29:09,314 --> 00:29:12,817
Let's forget it. Forget it, Hye-seong.

359
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:43,782
Thank you.

360
00:30:33,865 --> 00:30:37,468
It's too dark.
Why aren't there streetlights?

361
00:30:38,336 --> 00:30:41,139
Let's go around.
I'll think of it as exercise.

362
00:30:52,483 --> 00:30:56,621
You're the one who just moved in, right?

363
00:30:56,855 --> 00:31:00,158
-Do you like the place?
-What do you think?

364
00:31:03,127 --> 00:31:04,829
Can you see the cards in the dark?

365
00:31:05,930 --> 00:31:09,701
Even if it's dark,
I can still see money and cards.

366
00:31:10,101 --> 00:31:12,704
-When are they fixing the streetlights?
-No idea.

367
00:31:12,804 --> 00:31:15,840
I called the local government office,
but they directed me to city hall.

368
00:31:16,007 --> 00:31:19,777
So I called today, and
they told me to call another department.

369
00:31:19,878 --> 00:31:22,947
So I called them,
but they told me to call someone else.

370
00:31:23,047 --> 00:31:25,316
So at last I called them,
but everyone had gone home.

371
00:31:26,918 --> 00:31:31,122
Anyway, they will fix it soon!
Don't you worry!

372
00:31:31,256 --> 00:31:35,093
-Mom, the show has started. Hurry!
-The show?

373
00:31:36,361 --> 00:31:37,195
The show!

374
00:32:28,780 --> 00:32:30,815
MOM

375
00:32:32,083 --> 00:32:34,319
-It's me.
-Yes, Mom.

376
00:32:34,786 --> 00:32:36,487
How was your day?

377
00:32:36,721 --> 00:32:38,756
Nothing much happened.

378
00:32:39,357 --> 00:32:42,226
You said there are
three men in your office.

379
00:32:42,894 --> 00:32:45,163
Isn't there anyone you might want to date?

380
00:32:45,797 --> 00:32:47,765
No, there isn't any. They're all losers.

381
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:51,469
They're a mix of the worst guys ever.

382
00:32:52,203 --> 00:32:54,839
Why? Do they look down on you?

383
00:32:56,307 --> 00:32:57,709
No.

384
00:32:58,810 --> 00:33:02,480
It's not like that.
But they're loud and tiresome.

385
00:33:04,582 --> 00:33:08,686
Why do you sound so down?
Did something happen?

386
00:33:10,054 --> 00:33:12,957
No. I'm okay.

387
00:33:14,225 --> 00:33:16,260
You don't sound okay.

388
00:33:17,028 --> 00:33:18,730
Shall I go see you tomorrow?

389
00:33:19,497 --> 00:33:23,201
I'm really okay. It's nothing.

390
00:33:27,605 --> 00:33:29,707
It's because of the broken streetlights.

391
00:33:30,208 --> 00:33:31,642
"Streetlights"?

392
00:33:32,810 --> 00:33:36,981
Yes, the streetlights.
I don't like the dark.

393
00:33:38,216 --> 00:33:39,584
That's why.

394
00:33:43,721 --> 00:33:46,424
The streetlights just came back on.

395
00:33:47,125 --> 00:33:49,727
Really? Maybe someone fixed them.

396
00:33:50,628 --> 00:33:52,330
No way. At this hour?

397
00:33:52,730 --> 00:33:57,735
Never mind. Go to sleep now.
It's your first trial tomorrow.

398
00:33:58,403 --> 00:34:01,572
All right. Good night, Mom.

399
00:34:02,140 --> 00:34:05,543
Sure. Have a great dream.

400
00:34:34,572 --> 00:34:38,042
What is this?
Did someone fix it at this hour?

401
00:35:06,804 --> 00:35:09,373
I guess our civil officials
aren't that bad.

402
00:35:38,603 --> 00:35:39,770
Ko Seong-bin?

403
00:35:47,578 --> 00:35:49,046
How could this happen?

404
00:35:50,515 --> 00:35:54,886
I didn't do anything.
Why won't anyone listen to me?

405
00:35:56,020 --> 00:35:59,624
Attempted murder?
I will go to jail, right?

406
00:36:01,325 --> 00:36:02,693
Jail.

407
00:36:04,328 --> 00:36:05,963
Should I just die?

408
00:36:07,365 --> 00:36:13,070
My friends, my lawyer. No one believes me.

409
00:36:14,272 --> 00:36:15,806
What's the use of living?

410
00:36:17,542 --> 00:36:19,443
Will they believe me if I just die?

411
00:36:20,845 --> 00:36:22,413
Will they regret not believing me?

412
00:36:26,851 --> 00:36:29,020
Ko Seong-bin!

413
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:33,991
Stay right there. I'll be right there.

414
00:36:35,159 --> 00:36:36,894
Will Su-ha cry for me?

415
00:36:38,696 --> 00:36:42,900
No, he won't even notice that I'm gone.

416
00:36:46,137 --> 00:36:49,774
Don't be silly, Seong-bin!
Stay right there.

417
00:37:19,670 --> 00:37:24,075
Ko Seong-bin! No! Don't do it! Don't!

418
00:37:30,381 --> 00:37:32,683
You idiot! What are you doing?

419
00:37:35,286 --> 00:37:38,956
Su-ha.

420
00:38:00,177 --> 00:38:01,078
Thank you.

421
00:38:03,581 --> 00:38:06,884
Did you hear about what happened?

422
00:38:08,719 --> 00:38:11,155
-Yes.
-Do you think that Double Nose...

423
00:38:12,890 --> 00:38:16,160
Do you think that I pushed Dong-hui?

424
00:38:17,194 --> 00:38:19,563
-No.
-Liar.

425
00:38:20,898 --> 00:38:22,833
He is just saying that
because I might kill myself.

426
00:38:23,768 --> 00:38:26,671
I really believe you. You didn't do it.

427
00:38:28,172 --> 00:38:29,940
Thanks a bunch.

428
00:38:34,578 --> 00:38:36,047
Did you meet a lawyer?

429
00:38:38,015 --> 00:38:42,853
Yes, I wish my lawyer would believe me
like you do.

430
00:38:43,621 --> 00:38:45,056
Who is your lawyer?

431
00:38:46,490 --> 00:38:48,526
Why? Will you beat her up for me?

432
00:38:48,993 --> 00:38:51,362
If it's necessary, I will. Who is it?

433
00:38:51,862 --> 00:38:55,232
She is a public defender. Jang Hye-seong.

434
00:38:56,367 --> 00:38:58,969
Jang Hye-seong?

435
00:38:59,070 --> 00:39:02,173
Yes, her surname is Jang
and her name is Hye-seong.

436
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:04,342
She just came to Yeonju.

