00:41:59,483 --> 00:42:01,652
That's right.

474
00:42:01,752 --> 00:42:07,825
But my mother is still alive
inside my heart.

475
00:42:07,892 --> 00:42:09,226
Inside your heart?

476
00:42:11,762 --> 00:42:18,035
You used the knife
because the police sexually harassed you.

477
00:42:18,969 --> 00:42:21,872
I am ashamed, but it just happened.

478
00:42:22,006 --> 00:42:23,374
Objection.

479
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:27,211
The police officers
who arrested the defendant

480
00:42:27,278 --> 00:42:29,046
were all female.

481
00:42:34,318 --> 00:42:36,620
Were the police officers all female?

482
00:42:37,454 --> 00:42:40,257
Yes, that's right. They were women,

483
00:42:40,491 --> 00:42:43,861
but they were just as strong as men.

484
00:42:58,676 --> 00:43:01,912
Thank you for letting me
watch your trial, Mr. Cha.

485
00:43:03,814 --> 00:43:05,649
I learned a lot today.

486
00:43:06,250 --> 00:43:09,353
I learned how dangerous it is
to trust your defendant blindly.

487
00:43:09,453 --> 00:43:14,992
And I also realized how incompetent
a lawyer can be without expertise.

488
00:43:15,559 --> 00:43:16,594
Thank you.

489
00:43:22,132 --> 00:43:24,969
Don't you think
she has a strange personality?

490
00:43:25,269 --> 00:43:28,539
It's as if she is determined
to make people hate her!

491
00:43:28,672 --> 00:43:31,375
-She has the wrong kind of face.
-Right?

492
00:43:31,976 --> 00:43:35,145
By the way, I feel so bad
for Jo Yeong-sook.

493
00:43:35,279 --> 00:43:39,016
She lives in a semi-basement studio,
but it got flooded by the rain.

494
00:43:39,183 --> 00:43:42,019
She now lives in a tin shack.
Why would she ever lie?

495
00:43:46,290 --> 00:43:49,827
Do you think all poor people are good?

496
00:43:50,761 --> 00:43:52,596
Do you think all poor people are wronged?

497
00:43:53,631 --> 00:43:55,899
-What?
-Okay, so she is poor.

498
00:43:56,667 --> 00:43:59,370
What if someone
who isn't wronged comes to you?

499
00:44:00,437 --> 00:44:01,772
Well...

500
00:44:03,707 --> 00:44:08,479
People come to us because either
they took money or someone's life.

501
00:44:08,946 --> 00:44:12,483
Most of them are criminals
who aren't worth defending.

502
00:44:12,683 --> 00:44:15,252
But it's not
as if we can choose not to defend them.

503
00:44:15,386 --> 00:44:17,755
If that happens to you,
how will you defend them?

504
00:44:21,625 --> 00:44:24,294
-Well?
-I'm not sure.

505
00:44:45,582 --> 00:44:48,552
Ko Seong-bin, this is Su-ha.
Are you on your way to the court?

506
00:44:48,752 --> 00:44:49,753
Yes.

507
00:44:49,887 --> 00:44:52,656
Just come straight here.
I'll go inside with you.

508
00:44:52,890 --> 00:44:53,957
Thank you.

509
00:45:01,231 --> 00:45:03,200
Are you really Ko Seong-bin?

510
00:45:05,936 --> 00:45:09,740
Yes. I'm going to try not to swear.

511
00:45:11,675 --> 00:45:13,110
Let's go in.

512
00:45:17,081 --> 00:45:19,550
ESTABLISHING PUBLIC ORDER

513
00:45:25,422 --> 00:45:28,058
-Are you going to the trial?
-Yes.

514
00:45:37,034 --> 00:45:38,035
ELEVATOR TO TRIAL COURT

515
00:45:40,204 --> 00:45:43,874
I'm about to begin a trial.
Do you have anything to tell me?

516
00:45:48,545 --> 00:45:50,147
Of course you don't.

517
00:46:03,093 --> 00:46:06,730
Isn't it normal for the last person
to get on to get off in this case?

518
00:46:13,070 --> 00:46:14,338
Mr. Shin!

519
00:46:30,454 --> 00:46:33,991
What are you doing here, Hye-seong?

520
00:46:35,559 --> 00:46:37,294
What about you?

521
00:46:39,963 --> 00:46:41,565
Are you a prosecutor?

522
00:46:42,833 --> 00:46:45,602
I heard from Yeon-jin
that you had become a lawyer.

523
00:46:46,203 --> 00:46:47,871
I didn't realize we would meet like this.

524
00:46:48,038 --> 00:46:50,774
Did you start a business?
Or are you with a law firm?

525
00:46:51,441 --> 00:46:56,113
No, I'm not a private lawyer.
I'm a public defender.

526
00:46:56,980 --> 00:46:59,216
You're a public defender.

527
00:47:00,684 --> 00:47:03,420
We may meet in court.

528
00:47:04,288 --> 00:47:07,858
I guess so. I hope we meet.

529
00:47:10,794 --> 00:47:12,429
COURT OF KOREA

530
00:47:12,496 --> 00:47:13,931
Ms. Jang!

531
00:47:15,732 --> 00:47:17,234
I'm not late, right?

532
00:47:20,671 --> 00:47:23,841
You were here, too, Ms. Seo.

533
00:47:24,341 --> 00:47:27,411
Are you Ko Seong-bin's lawyer?

534
00:47:27,678 --> 00:47:33,417
Are you the prosecutor for this trial?

535
00:47:58,442 --> 00:47:59,576
SEO DO-YEON

536
00:48:02,012 --> 00:48:05,349
Seo Do-yeon. Why didn't I see that?

537
00:48:08,518 --> 00:48:09,853
I saw it, too.

538
00:48:10,254 --> 00:48:12,055
I saw Hye-seong
pointing the firework at me.

539
00:48:13,290 --> 00:48:14,324
Hey!

540
00:48:14,858 --> 00:48:19,029
How can you take it?
Aren't you mad? I got expelled today.

541
00:48:19,830 --> 00:48:22,666
I got kicked out
even though I didn't do anything.

542
00:48:22,766 --> 00:48:25,102
No, I didn't see it.

543
00:48:25,402 --> 00:48:27,838
You kept lying,
so I lied to make you confess.

544
00:48:28,472 --> 00:48:30,007
Then prove it.

545
00:48:30,607 --> 00:48:32,843
I'll admit it if you go
and testify in court.

546
00:48:33,477 --> 00:48:35,045
I'll admit that you're not a liar.

547
00:48:51,161 --> 00:48:53,397
Seong-bin. Let's talk.

548
00:48:59,369 --> 00:49:02,773
-Why is this guy following you?
-He is my friend.

549
00:49:04,341 --> 00:49:08,178
Hey, I really need to focus.
So please stay here. Alright?

550
00:49:14,551 --> 00:49:19,256
Okay, take a look at this.
It's what I'm going to ask you.

551
00:49:19,423 --> 00:49:20,991
Read it.

552
00:49:22,292 --> 00:49:26,797
No, don't read it.
Just say, "Yes," when I question you.

553
00:49:26,863 --> 00:49:28,432
Just "Yes." Got it?

554
00:49:28,632 --> 00:49:31,635
No, I didn't push her.
I'm going to tell the truth.

555
00:49:31,735 --> 00:49:34,671
No, you can't do that.
You saw the prosecutor, right?

556
00:49:34,905 --> 00:49:37,808
If she finds fault in us,
you and I are both doomed.

557
00:49:38,008 --> 00:49:41,144
You could make things worse
by offending her.

558
00:49:41,411 --> 00:49:42,813
And I'll be embarrassed.

559
00:49:42,913 --> 00:49:47,317
I can't let that happen.
So say you're guilty and sorry.

560
00:49:47,517 --> 00:49:51,788
And ask for mercy.
That's the best way, okay?

561
00:49:55,292 --> 00:49:56,560
What are you doing?

562
00:49:56,793 --> 00:49:59,997
Seong-bin, go ahead. We need to talk.

563
00:50:00,097 --> 00:50:02,632
Let me go! Let go!

564
00:50:03,333 --> 00:50:07,070
Hey! Put me down! Hey!

565
00:50:07,371 --> 00:50:12,075
Hey! Who are you? Put me down!

566
00:50:16,413 --> 00:50:19,016
Let go of me! You just took me by force.

567
00:50:19,249 --> 00:50:22,853
There are security cameras.
You'll be punished for this!

568
00:50:27,624 --> 00:50:31,862
Let me go. Calm down. Let's be rational.

569
00:50:31,995 --> 00:50:33,096
Seong-bin is innocent.

570
00:50:33,730 --> 00:50:36,299
-What?
-So you should prove it.

571
00:50:37,367 --> 00:50:40,404
Who are you? Why are you being so rude?

572
00:50:44,107 --> 00:50:45,509
I'm Seong-bin's classmate.

573
00:50:47,944 --> 00:50:51,381
Do you know anything about the case?
Were you at the scene?

574
00:50:51,848 --> 00:50:54,351
Seong-bin tried to kill herself yesterday
after meeting you.

575
00:51:00,390 --> 00:51:03,326
So what? Do you think that's evidence?

576
00:51:03,827 --> 00:51:04,795
You're the worst.

577
00:51:06,329 --> 00:51:07,564
Are you really a lawyer?

578
00:51:09,366 --> 00:51:11,568
Who are you trying to preach to?

579
00:51:11,668 --> 00:51:14,438
You just kidnapped me,
and now you're trying to preach me?

580
00:51:14,504 --> 00:51:15,906
Where did you learn your manners?

581
00:51:16,006 --> 00:51:18,742
-Behave yourself.
-You should behave yourself.

582
00:51:19,109 --> 00:51:21,278
Shouldn't a lawyer listen to her client?

583
00:51:21,378 --> 00:51:25,048
How are you different
from a prosecutor if you don't?

584
00:51:25,148 --> 00:51:26,883
There is no evidence.

585
00:51:27,017 --> 00:51:29,753
There's only evidence proving her guilt.

586
00:51:30,020 --> 00:51:32,189
Bring me evidence if you want to fight me.

587
00:51:32,355 --> 00:51:34,524
-I have evidence.
-What is it?

588
00:51:39,262 --> 00:51:40,864
Why are you looking at me like that?

589
00:51:42,632 --> 00:51:45,735
-If you stare--
-"If you stare, will proof appear?"

590
00:51:49,806 --> 00:51:52,375
-What is this? How did you do that?
-"What is this? How did you do that?"

591
00:51:54,611 --> 00:51:56,847
-Do you know what I'll say?
-"Do you know what I'll say?"

592
00:52:05,555 --> 00:52:06,756
No way.

593
00:52:13,096 --> 00:52:16,766
I can read other people's minds.
That's my evidence.

594
00:52:40,123 --> 00:52:42,526
ATTEMPTED MURDER

595
00:52:48,365 --> 00:52:50,133
ARTICLE 250 OF THE CONSTITUTION
ATTEMPTED MURDER...

596
00:52:52,102 --> 00:52:55,539
Are you just going to stand there?
You have to go help Seong-bin.

597
00:52:56,806 --> 00:52:57,908
Don't come near me.

598
00:53:00,911 --> 00:53:02,379
How is this possible?

599
00:53:04,781 --> 00:53:06,416
Don't look at me as if I were a monster.

600
00:53:06,983 --> 00:53:11,087
Some people have an IQ of 200
and some run 100 meters in nine seconds.

601
00:53:12,189 --> 00:53:14,524
Being special doesn't
mean that we're monsters.

602
00:53:15,058 --> 00:53:18,662
You're so childish.
I'm not an alien. I was born here.

603
00:53:18,828 --> 00:53:20,730
Did you read my mind again?

604
00:53:21,364 --> 00:53:24,100
Don't read it! It feels really creepy.

605
00:53:24,334 --> 00:53:25,969
I don't want to know either.

606
00:53:26,102 --> 00:53:28,004
But I hear your thoughts
when I look into your eyes.

607
00:53:29,272 --> 00:53:33,810
Shoot. Should I report this?
This is an invasion of my privacy.

608
00:53:34,945 --> 00:53:38,348
Concentrate on Seong-bin.
How will you prove her innocence?

609
00:53:40,417 --> 00:53:42,752
Lips can lie, but hearts cannot lie.

610
00:53:43,053 --> 00:53:46,923
She is innocent. I heard it.
So you have to prove it.

611
00:53:48,258 --> 00:53:49,593
I can't do it.

612
00:53:50,093 --> 00:53:53,196
-You won't have her plead not guilty?
-No, I just can't do it.

613
00:53:53,296 --> 00:53:54,598
There is no evidence.

614
00:53:56,533 --> 00:53:59,302
I said I'm the evidence. I heard her.

615
00:54:00,737 --> 00:54:02,105
Will you go on the stand, then?

616
00:54:02,272 --> 00:54:05,575
Will you testify that you read her mind
and that she is innocent?

617
00:54:06,743 --> 00:54:10,080
Do you think the judge
and prosecutor will be impressed

618
00:54:10,146 --> 00:54:13,550
by your mind-reading skills, believe it,
and accept it as evidence?

619
00:54:13,617 --> 00:54:15,685
You and I will be kicked out
for being crazy.

620
00:54:24,127 --> 00:54:28,498
See? He is lying that
he can read people's minds.

621
00:54:31,001 --> 00:54:35,171
And let's pretend that
they did accept it as evidence.

622
00:54:35,805 --> 00:54:37,207
What if you're lying?

623
00:54:37,807 --> 00:54:40,010
-I don't lie.
-How would we know that?

624
00:54:40,343 --> 00:54:44,614
Other people can't read minds.
How will you prove it in court?

625
00:54:45,749 --> 00:54:48,351
That's why you won't
be admitted as evidence.

626
00:54:48,885 --> 00:54:52,289
Your ability is amazing,
but it won't help us now.

627
00:54:52,622 --> 00:54:56,259
Knowing the truth is not what's important
at trial.

628
00:54:56,926 --> 00:54:59,329
What's important is
whether there is evidence.

629
00:55:03,633 --> 00:55:04,567
What about the truth?

630
00:55:08,838 --> 00:55:12,342
Doesn't the truth win in court?

631
00:55:12,809 --> 00:55:15,745
Of course not. It's the other way around.

632
00:55:16,112 --> 00:55:20,717
Truth doesn't win in court.
Whatever wins in court is the truth.

633
00:55:56,219 --> 00:55:57,954
I will protect you.

634
00:56:21,277 --> 00:56:22,879
I will protect you.

635
00:56:43,333 --> 00:56:45,468
How does he read minds?

636
00:56:46,503 --> 00:56:47,937
That's amazing.

637
00:56:48,605 --> 00:56:50,640
Never mind. Forget it.

638
00:56:51,574 --> 00:56:54,544
Just think about Seo Do-yeon.

639
00:56:56,880 --> 00:56:57,981
Why are you thinking about me?

640
00:57:02,218 --> 00:57:04,354
I was so surprised
that I didn't even say hello.

641
00:57:05,288 --> 00:57:08,291
-How long has it been?
-Ten years?

642
00:57:09,192 --> 00:57:11,928
I think I last saw you in court.

643
00:57:13,163 --> 00:57:16,533
Do you remember?
You ran away and never came.

644
00:57:16,800 --> 00:57:17,767
Did I?

645
00:57:21,137 --> 00:57:23,907
I thought I would have a lot
to tell you if I met you.

646
00:57:24,941 --> 00:57:26,176
But I can't remember.

647
00:57:27,777 --> 00:57:29,946
I didn't know we would run
into each other like this.

648
00:57:31,147 --> 00:57:34,818
I know. A prosecutor and a lawyer.

649
00:57:36,052 --> 00:57:38,855
The world is so small and funny, isn't it?

650
00:57:47,764 --> 00:57:50,133
How will your client plead?

651
00:57:50,467 --> 00:57:52,135
Not guilty?

652
00:57:58,942 --> 00:58:03,012
No, you wrote one bloody arraignment.

653
00:58:03,213 --> 00:58:07,016
There's no way out of it.
Who would plead not guilty?

654
00:58:07,250 --> 00:58:10,954
Why? You should at least try.
I think there might be a chance.

655
00:58:11,754 --> 00:58:16,860
No, I don't want to be embarrassed
in front of an old classmate.

656
00:58:22,098 --> 00:58:23,700
You're so much alike.

657
00:58:24,634 --> 00:58:28,037
-With whom?
-Nothing. See you later.

658
00:58:28,671 --> 00:58:29,806
Okay.

659
00:58:34,711 --> 00:58:36,346
Are you reading my mind again?

660
00:58:37,714 --> 00:58:40,817
-Who is that?
-None of your business.

661
00:58:41,017 --> 00:58:43,353
Let's stay away from each other, okay?

662
00:58:44,153 --> 00:58:46,789
What is the firework incident?

663
00:58:48,825 --> 00:58:50,326
How do you know about it?

664
00:58:50,426 --> 00:58:52,228
I read her mind.

665
00:58:56,032 --> 00:58:59,068
Tell me more about what she was thinking.

666
00:59:05,241 --> 00:59:07,043
YEONJU DISTRICT PROSECUTOR'S OFFICE

667
00:59:11,114 --> 00:59:13,016
She said Seong-bin is very much like you.

668
00:59:13,850 --> 00:59:16,019
How you were ten years ago
when the firework incident happened.

669
00:59:16,185 --> 00:59:17,787
You're so much alike.

670
00:59:27,964 --> 00:59:30,700
Isn't that the new public defender?

671
00:59:30,833 --> 00:59:34,571
-Wasn't she in the news?
-What? Yes.

672
00:59:34,938 --> 00:59:39,442
Isn't she the one who got hired
because of her story?

673
00:59:39,576 --> 00:59:41,210
You said she seems like a good lawyer.

674
00:59:52,855 --> 00:59:54,657
Shoot.

675
00:59:57,527 --> 01:00:00,597
She looked nice back then.

676
01:00:01,497 --> 01:00:03,933
Shoot.

677
01:00:04,000 --> 01:00:05,568
IN SESSION

678
01:00:11,674 --> 01:00:13,676
ATTORNEY'S SEAT, DEFENDANT'S SEAT

679
01:00:18,815 --> 01:00:20,450
Make your statement.

680
01:00:21,250 --> 01:00:25,154
Ko Seong-bin was a classmate
of Mun Dong-hui.

681
01:00:25,288 --> 01:00:28,057
She always bullied
and harassed the victim.

682
01:00:28,591 --> 01:00:34,397
She was jealous the victim got picked up
by an agency.

683
01:00:35,098 --> 01:00:38,234
And she pushed the victim
when she was sitting by the window.

684
01:00:39,202 --> 01:00:44,374
The victim has multiple injuries
all over her body.

685
01:00:44,540 --> 01:00:47,210
She is currently lying unconscious
in the hospital.

686
01:00:47,543 --> 01:00:51,114
Based on Articles 250 and 254

687
01:00:51,247 --> 01:00:56,252
of the Penal Code, Ko Seong-bin is
hereby charged with attempted murder.

688
01:01:15,505 --> 01:01:20,576
Are you sure that she is innocent?

689
01:01:23,746 --> 01:01:27,817
Can I believe you?

690
01:01:33,022 --> 01:01:36,426
It's your turn, Counsel.

691
01:01:37,794 --> 01:01:39,128
Counsel!

692
01:01:39,862 --> 01:01:42,265
-Yes?
-Do you agree with the indictment?

693
01:02:02,719 --> 01:02:05,488
I do not agree with the indictment at all.

694
01:02:10,727 --> 01:02:13,596
The defendant is pleading not guilty.

695
01:02:28,745 --> 01:02:30,780
